This paper deals with the task of discovering user intents from user query utterances in human-human conversations, which is a common problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel deep multi-view clustering approach, which involves machine learning techniques such as representation learning and clustering analysis, making it relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and analysis of human-human conversations, which could fall under categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
